Comparator → Sorting business objects (employees, orders, products).

: Java’s Comparator Interface

The Comparator interface (from java.util) has static methods 
like comparing(), naturalOrder(), and reverseOrder() 
that are heavily used in sorting real-world data.


Predicate → Conditional checks in authentication, validation, workflows.

Stream → Data pipelines in finance, IoT, reporting.

Collectors → Aggregation in analytics and dashboards.

Optional → Safe handling of nulls in enterprise systems.

Function.identity() → Simplifies mapping in ETL/data processing apps.